        Estimates the probability that a temporal property (tx_from, tx_to, valid_from, valid_to) of an element with a certain label satisfies a constraint comparing it to a literal
        Parameters:
        type1 - the type of the element to compare (vertex or edge)
        label1 - label of the element to compare (if known)
        field1 - time field (tx_from, tx_to, valid_from, valid_to) of the element to compare
        comp - comparator
        value - long constant (i.e. literal) to compare the element with
        Returns:
        estimation of the probability that the condition holds

      • estimateTemporalProb

        public abstract double estimateTemporalProb(TemporalGraphStatistics.ElementType type1,
                                            Optional<String> label1,
                                            org.gradoop.gdl.model.comparables.time.TimeSelector.TimeField field1,
                                            org.gradoop.gdl.utils.Comparator comp,
                                            TemporalGraphStatistics.ElementType type2,
                                            Optional<String> label2,
                                            org.gradoop.gdl.model.comparables.time.TimeSelector.TimeField field2)
        Estimates the probability that a comparison between two time selectors holds. The return value may only be reasonable, if the time selectors refer to distinct variables.
        Parameters:
        type1 - the type of the lhs element to compare (vertex or edge)
        label1 - label of the lhs element to compare (if known)
        field1 - time property (tx_from, tx_to, valid_from, valid_to) of the lhs element to compare
        comp - comparator
        type2 - the type of the rhs element to compare (vertex or edge)
        label2 - label of the rhs element to compare (if known)
        field2 - time property (tx_from, tx_to, val_from, val_to) of the rhs element to compare
        Returns:
        estimation of the probability that the condition holds

        Estimates the probability that a comparison of the form variable.interval comparator constant holds.
        Parameters:
        type - type of the lhs element (vertex/edge)
        label - label of the lhs element
        comp - comparator of the comparison

        value - lhs duration constant
        Returns:
        estimated probability that the comparison holds
